{
  "message": "fuzz: expand btrfs chunk mapping and ext4 checksum seed corpora\n\nFinal batch of corpus expansion for security-critical parsers:\n\nfuzz_btrfs_chunk_mapping (was 2 seeds, now 6):\n- Single stripe configuration\n- RAID0 and RAID1 profiles\n- Random entropy seed\n\nfuzz_ext4_checksums (was 2 seeds, now 6):\n- Different inode sizes (132/256 bytes)\n- Directory block checksum path\n- Random entropy seed\n\nThese seeds ensure better initial coverage for the chunk translation\nlayer (critical for multi-device btrfs) and metadata integrity\nverification (critical for detecting corruption).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
